caption: This was my first experience and it was great. My family of 3 enjoyed the food and I personal recommend the chicken and waffles and the Cajun fries. We will definitely come again to feed our souls, lady but not least, customer service was awesome ☺️
Chicken and waffles were fire

Good food, great vibe. Being trans-southern I never have high expectations for southern style food in NYC. But they did not disappoint the fried ribs were so tender and tasty I want to duplicate at home.

To put it simply, my dining experience at Kind of Soul was exquisite perfection. The chicken and waffles was delicious and juicy. I usually struggle to finish a meal but I completely finished my catfish entree. The mac and cheese was excellent. The KOS burger was perfection with the andouille sausage. Our server, a young lady, was also very kind and attentive. I will definitely be coming back soon and telling everyone about this place!
The ribs are the best ribs I ever had, hands down, my mouth is watering now as i write this, so good.  They also have done in again although its it's only bbv 2 tables

I have never had Japanese curry dishes, a new cuisine for me. I ordered the regular curry with Tofu. My dish was so good and plated nicely. My husband had the regular curry with potato croquettes, delicious. The curry sauce had such a rich flavor, yummy pickled veggies. We look forward to trying other dishes. They have a selection of Japanese craft beers, very good. I had a glass of cold sake, went well with my dish.

My absolute favorite place for Shrimp & Grits! Fried ribs slide right off the bone! Salmon is bomb and to top it off 😋 EXCELLENT SERVICE from all EMPLOYEES! That's how you do BLACK OWNED BUSINESS RIGHT 🙌🏾☝🏾👏🏿
What an awesome restaurant! The food 🥘, vibe🔥, drinks 🍸 all 💯 ✊🏿✊🏿✊🏿✊🏿✊🏿 🦍🦍🦍🦍🦍
Been meaning to write a review the food was amazing! Oh and the cocktails🔥 they did not scrimp on the alcohol

What a nice cozy spot. I'm a sucker for good atmosphere and this place I has it with their outdoor seating. Food was good, nothing that would make me run back here but it was good for what it was. The person I was with loved the ribs though and I did enjoy the shrimp & grits. Drinks were also good, well made and a decent amount. My only knock would be the pricing — you'll pay a pretty penny for some good eats.  Definitely would come again. I'd use this place as a way to show off all the dope spots in the area.

I like the Coco Mojito. I like the waffle more than the chicken probably because they gave me chicken breast. The waffle is good enough that I want to ask for the receipt. Overall, the chicken is crispy outside, not over cook inside, but still too well done to my taste. Perhaps it would be better to use chicken tender strip, thinner cut of meat.  I found out at the end that I could have asked for dark meat instead.
Yum! Attentive staff and carefully crafted food await you at this small soul food spot. Came here for brunch with family (in the backyard ✨) and left very satisfied with my meal. Def will be back!

The "outdoor dining area" is a backyard adjacent to residential homes. Loud conversations and blasting music from early afternoon to late night permeate the houses nearby.  No soundproofing whatsoever. I wish the owners and patrons were more considerate towards the neighborhood.
Awesome menu. Awesome caring staff! Wonderful libation creations. Great gem.
Awesome food, great atmosphere

I was looking for a place I could take one of my friends out for her birthday and stumbled across this spot. I picked it because it had vegan options. I called in and made reservations with a nice gentleman. When I arrived the server took my name and sat us in this cute area in the back. The server was very nice and attentive.  I ordered a gnocchi gumbo (no meat) and a strawberry martini. My friend ordered the chicken and waffles and a passion fruit martini. My food was good and the martini was very sweet but not bad. My friend said her food was ok and enjoyed her drink.  A nice gentleman heard it was my friend's birthday and without us knowing ordered a peach cobbler. That was super nice of him. The peach cobbler was very tasty. All in all I had a good experience.

Came here with some colleagues today. Food was pretty good, service was quick. But towards the end of our visit, 3 things happened. One, the server removed all our water glasses. As someone that worked in service for years, that's a very rude move. It tells customers to get tf out. Two, the server spilled my beer while clearing our water glasses. There was about a third of it left. I wasn't offered a replacement. Third, he took our credit card receipt off the table before we left.  Retrain your employees, please.

Well first I want to say during the COVID pandemic this is one of the very few places open for dine in with lovely outdoor seating so that’s already a plus. Me and my friends went on a Saturday, I had crab cakes appetizer and chicken and waffles. They had shrimp and grits and the southern chicken sandwich and the fried cauliflower appetizer and the crab mac and cheese. My food was awesome, the crab cakes and sauce was really good. My waffle was perfect, crispy on the outside and fluffy on the inside. My friends loved their food as well. One of them liked the cauliflower so much she got another one to go and I came back the next day. We also got mixed drinks which were perfect. Service, atmosphere, and food were great. Check it out, you won’t be disappointed
Great food and breezy outdoor backyard dining.

I don't write a lot of reviews, so when I do it usually means I was really impressed.  This place knocked my socks off.  My friend and I were going to comedy show a few doors down (Pre-Covid) and needed something nearby to eat.  We looked over the menu and found the prices were reasonable and the selection had some delicious items.  We went inside and were seated immediately.  The bartender/waiter, Laurence, was knowledgeable and very friendly.  We started with the fried cauliflower appetizer and a couple drinks.  This fried cauliflower was amazing.  I could have wrote a whole review just based on this.  Happily, the chicken sandwich I ordered and the burger my friend got were both above expectations and we left completely satisfied.  If you have the chance definitely check this place out.
Fried chicken and biscuit and Caeser salad were fantastic. Great service. Nice addition to the neighborhood.

Delicious Southern-style food with a unique taste-Excellent Service- Great Ambience  I came across this restaurant, very last minute for my Mom Birthday, yesterday. So glad I chose the right restaurant.  I enjoyed everything here; the food was so good, chicken seasoned with flavor,  great quality wine and I cannot leave out those buttermilk homemade biscuits. Soft and buttery(thinking about it and want one now 😋) My family enjoyed it, too. Plates were definitely cleaned. I was unable to eat dessert, yet, my mom loved her carrot cake.  Met one of owners and he was down-to-earth and a great attitude. That is a must!  Can't wait to return for those biscuits and trying other dish. Great jobs guys and many successful years in Brooklyn!!!
Loved it!

This place really suprised us. Stumbled in on a whim and the food was amazing. I'm a vegetarian...and had the cauliflower, mushrooms and mashed potatoes. Hubby had the fried chicken and said it was the best he's had in Bk. We will absolutely be back!

I visited this place and had the opportunity to meet one of the owners, a very pleasant young man by the name of Ammar.  As for the food, I ordered the crab cakes, very good. The deep fried ribs, OMG,Finger licking delicious. Also the po'boy sandwich w/catfish had to be good because my friend devoured it, LOL.  Any who, I would definitely recommend you visiting this place. The food is great and the atmosphere is very friendly and laid back. You are guaranteed to have a good time.
Really liked this place. Our food (fried cauliflower, beet salad, gnocci gumbo) was really well prepared and well balanced with bold flavors that let the fresh ingredients star.
The service here is exceptional, the staff definitely made us feel at home, great conversation, and good food. The wings were great and the KOS burger is a hit! I will definitely be back. Thank you!

I must say the customer service is excellent. When you walk in your quickly greeted warmly with heartwarming words and smiles. Quaint and homely space. However, the food was something different. We had the fried chicken and macaroni and cheese. The chicken was not a crisp golden brown. It was rather dark and no real flavor we could not eat it. The macaroni and cheese was tangy and creamy not to my baked soul food expectations at all. The waffles my son had were delicious. They were fluffy, fresh soft and moist. The passion fruit syrup delicious. I paid $28 for the meal and had to buy food somewhere else..
Great food and great vibe
Great fried chicken and amazing collards. The servers very very friendly and helpful. So happy to find a decent soul food place in NYC.

Stumbled upon this place just by walking by. No one was inside which made me  more intrigued. I ordered the chicken and waffles for the first time with a coconut mojito. My drink was just right, what I loved the most is, when I took my food to go and ate it the next morning my waffle wasn’t soggy and the chicken was still moist. The decor was nice and quaint, the music was current hits at a reasonable volume. Service was good too, they were attentive even with an empty place. I will definitely be coming back.

Biscuit was great. Wasnt the biggest fan of the crab mac something about it was overpowering. The ribs were good and the fried chicken was ok. Feel like I kinda came on a bad day being that all the reviews are good. Maybe I will try again on a weekend when demands are higher.
we stumbled upon this place one night on our way to the Madonna concert. the bartender was so friendly and we had a great time. I'd love to return and try the food.

I had the chicken and biscuit and my son got the chicken and waffles and they were amazing.  The biscuit is the best I’ve ever had and the chicken is smoked then fried providing various layers of flavor.  I would for sure return.

We had the fried chicken sandwich with Cajun fries, fish and chips, and the veggie burger with the salad.  All of it was delicious, especially the fried chicken sandwich and the Cajun fries.  The service was incredibly friendly and attentive.  Will return!
Good drinks, great food, nice friendly staff
Crab Mac with real  🦀, ribs that fall for ff the bone, wings with house made sauces you can't get anywhere else and amazing drinks...I'm always there for more can't get enough!!
Great service. Great food. Great location

I went to this place for a friend's birthday. The food was AMAZING. We started with the crabcakes and they were delicious. My husband ordered the Ribs with the crab mac & cheese. The ribs didn't survive. I ordered the buttermilk fried chicken wings with the homemade biscuit and coleslaw. Everything on my plate was delicious. You can tell the owners have a high standard on what food should be served. You taste the spices and ingredients that are well mixed, it's like eating a homecooked meal but with elegance . I recommend this place for a date night, friends gathering, anything. I am definitely coming back. Worth every penny. The drinks are good too. I had the rasberry ice rea. I tasted the rasberry flavor. Great customer service, beautifully uniquely decorated.
A taste of home...gourmet style
Super friendly service. Great lunch specials and a well poured cocktail.
Delicious southern-style catfish, burgers and smoked wings. Very reasonable lunch menu prices! A great new addition to the neighborhood. I've already been several times.
The southern fried chicken sandwich was fabulous!  Crisp, tender and the spice was just right
Great place to relax and eat
This place is incredible. I had the fried ribs and gnochi gumbo. Dessert was the handmade bourbon ice cream. Food is delicious, vibe is tight, and service is fantastic.

I have visited this relatively new restaurant here twice, and have been impressed both times.  Impressed with the service and with the food!!. The menu is a relatively simple one, but the turkey burger I had here during the first visit was delicious and the side salad was very good.  The ice tea was great too - obviously freshly made  and not from a can!  During the second visit I had the cranberry salad and it was excellent!  The decor is nice and bright and extremely clean.  The restaurant, while a bit narrow due to the size of the space, feel spacious, and there is definitely room for groups up to about 6 people.  Having lived in this neighborhood for years, I would say that this restaurant is a great new asset to the neighborhood!!!
Atmosphere is GREAT
Their food is heavenly..and service is excellent...finally a nice neighborhood resturant.
Fusion soul with a twist is delish!  I had the veggie burger and chips/fries, really good and really filling! The staff is friendly and professional.
Love love love. Extremely accommodating and the ambiance is great. Happy hour is dope and the staff was very attentive and personable. The food was great too.
Food is good. Great atmosphere. Drinks on point. Proceed nicely and it feels like home. What more could you really want in a place?
Love this new addition to the neighborhood. I've been a few times and patricianly dig the Buffalo wings which have a b bbq undertone. The burgers are also super tasty.

Went to thos place on accident. I was headed to another spot, but it wasn't my type of place. Decided to check this place out. Only been open 4 months, but the atmosphere was absolutely amazing. I would recommend anyone to go there. No ghetto people tho!
The food is everything here and plus nothing there is over 40 dollars
Greatest restaurant of all time imo
Cozy spot for after work drinks and eats. They also have $10 lunch specials If you happen to be around in the afternoon.
Best soul food in Brooklyn
I came here on Kristens' birthday it was lit. The best place on Atlantic avenue
Delicious, Delicious, Delicious! Had the Beet Salad and Fish n Chips. Very nice atmosphere, friendly staff, great addition to the neighborhood. Highly Recommend!
Nice small and quiet spot with nice music and great food

I was fortunate enough to come here three times during my stay in Brooklyn and was blown away by the amazing service, drinks and food!  They are new and worth a visit, everyone who works there goes above and beyond and we had a fantastic time!  Even accommodate vegan and gluten free!
Awesome place !!! Service was excellent. The fried rib is a must have.

OMG!! Randomly found this place!  We were not disappointed!  The vegan chicken and waffles was delicious.  The fried ribs... A treat.  The turkey burger... Very tasty.  The fried catfish was done well.  Will definitely be returning.

Kind of Soul, is just the perfect spot to have a nice dinner out. Only blocks away from the Barclay Center. The place is amazing, well lit, great music, friendly, attentive, and engaging staff. The food is mouth watering amazing. The salmon dinner, the chicken and waffles are so delicious. My wife and I have been here twice and we are looking forward to coming again.

We've been here twice already and the food and service has been nothing short of amazing!!! The salmon melts in your mouth, the chicken and waffles were seasoned and cooked to perfection, the house wings were out of this world and the catfish was just down home delicious!!! We will definitely be back!!

Service was good. But the food was pretty terrible. I ordered the fried chicken, took over 30 mins to make. After waiting and getting excited thinking I was going to get Authentic fried chicken.  i got my plate I noticed the chicken was over fried, and after eating the drum stick it. I couldn’t finish my food. The Seasoning was so off and my food was bland. I was better off going to KFC or Popeyes. Saving myself 14 dollars. I left hungry and ripped off. Even my side of mash potatoes that was way over priced was just terrible barely can taste the garlic.
Good food great service. Gouda grilled cheese cajun fries great value lunch special
Food, drinks and service are great. Pretty chill atmosphere. I had the chicken and waffles, chicken was season very well. Definitely worth trying.
Great experience, friendly staff, and good food!

Newer spot. But definitely not a 5 star dining experience. And I definitely wouldn’t come here for the drinks. Had the chicken and waffles entree after being explained that I would be receiving chicken breasts, the plate came out and I received a over cooked drumstick and one small over cooked breast. The waffle was cooked perfectly with decent syrup.   Bottom line this place charges premium pricing with less than average quality of food and drinks. I know rent is getting high in Brooklyn but I can’t see this place staying in biz unless there’s a major change with the grade of chicken their purchasing. I won’t be a repeat customer but, they provided a good vibe and great service. At the end of the day I felt robbed.

Wow, so let's start by saying that we weren't even planning on coming here but we read the menu and said why not. The service was fantastic and though the food took a little longer than I had first anticipated it didn't matter once we tasted it! Wow chicken & waffles, farfalle veggie pasta and an apple salad were Insanely good. Definite return for me! Bringing more people next time.
Great service, nice cocktails, and has great vegetarian options. The chicken fried cauliflower was dope. And their house made vegetarian black bean burger was awesome.
Love, love, love...

Based on my first visit I’d give KOS 3.5 stars, but I’m adding the extra half star for potential.  I, and a dining companion, visited KOS on their grand opening day. I expected balloons, music, food/drink specials, but nope... the atmosphere was one of a typical day in a typical restaurant. The only difference was, people (employees? Owners?) kept asking if we were enjoying our food/experience.  For an appetizer, we ordered the smoked BBQ wings. They were tasty and I was impressed by the amount of wings that we received and their size. I’d order them again. For my entree, I ordered the KOS burger, because it came recommended. Yeah, it’s a good burger, BUT, I felt that it was lacking a proper balance. Perhaps a butter pickle or two, or something else cold... crunchy... I don’t know.  The drinks were, for lack of a better word, forgettable. I ordered a bourbon drink from their mixed drink menu and wasn’t impressed. It was sweet and on the weaker side. My companion also ordered a mixed drink (lemonade?) and I could tell by her reaction that she wasn’t wowed by it. I’d probably skip the mixed drinks unless there was a a happy hour special.  Had I not ordered the KOS burger I was tempted to order their shrimp & grits. When I learned that their S&G didn’t come with a sauce or gravy that was an instant turn off for me.  On my next visit I’ll either go with the Southern Chicken Sandwich or the Chicken and waffles.  I know that I don’t sound thrilled by my first visit, I am looking forward to my second visit and I recommend that you check them out for yourself. KOS provides a welcome touch of originality in the land of quinoa bowls and overpriced coffee.
Very nice spot the food and drinks are awesome!!! I’ll be back again for sure
Great service amazing food... definitely a nice cozy spot to spend your evening. I reccomend trying the veggie burger
Gorgeous decor. I absolutely loved the chicken fried cauliflower and collard greens. The mule made with ginger beer was tasty and refreshing!!!!
Food was amazing service was great prices great decor 🧡🧡
Omg!!!!! Food was Great. Drinks was awesome. Owners came out and Greeted myself and my guest with warm smiles. This is definitely a spot I will revisit.
